A_635 - It may happen that when we were little our parents made mistakes in our presence but that in some cases we were not mature enough to understand the various aspects and the depth of certain situations. It could be important to think about our childhood and in particular about those situations that saw our parents or our relatives as protagonists and in which we have the feeling that something was not right, because in those situations there could be important issues to analyze, understand in detail and share with those around us.